<span id="freeTextContainer16714483880467236629">&quot;But here we&apos;re dealing with a collective experience, something foreseen and feared many times in advance, that happened to women right and left, all somehow part of the bargain. And this mass rape is something we are overcoming collectively as well. All the women help the other, by speaking about it, airing their pain and allowing others to air theirs and spit out what they&apos;ve suffered.&quot;<br/><br/>Extraordinary. Such a well-written, brave and honest account. This is a true horror story. The subject matter</span>
  <span id="freeText16714483880467236629" style="display:none">"But here we're dealing with a collective experience, something foreseen and feared many times in advance, that happened to women right and left, all somehow part of the bargain. And this mass rape is something we are overcoming collectively as well. All the women help the other, by speaking about it, airing their pain and allowing others to air theirs and spit out what they've suffered."<br /><br />Extraordinary. Such a well-written, brave and honest account. This is a true horror story. The subject matter is completely nauseating and appalling and I'm sad to say that I honestly had no idea that it even happened.<br /><br />I long to live in a matriarchal utopia where no woman is ever raped or forced to have sex, through coercion, societal pressure, or Goddess forbid, in order to exchange her body for food. It's horrifying and disgusting that sex has been used against women as a weapon for so long. <br /><br />Absolutely everyone should read this book. </span>
